{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 47,
  "title": "第四十七章（知天下）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "不出於戶，以知天下。"
    },
    {
      "text": "不窺於牖，以知天道。"
    },
    {
      "text": "其出也彌遠，其知彌少。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以聖人："
    },
    {
      "text": "不行而知。"
    },
    {
      "text": "不見而名。"
    },
    {
      "text": "弗為而成。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人不出戶以知天下者，以己身知人身，以己家知人家，所以見天下也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天道與人道同，天人相通，精氣相貫。人君清淨，天氣自正，人君多欲，天氣煩濁。吉兇利害，皆由於己。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂去其家觀人家，去其身觀人身，所觀益遠，所見益少也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人不上天，不入淵，能知天下者，以心知之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 12,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "上好道，下好德；上好武，下好力。聖人原小知大，察內知外。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 5,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "上無所為，則下無事，家給人足，萬物自化就也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "事有宗，而物有主，途雖殊而同歸也，慮雖百而其致一也。道有大常，理有大致，執古之道，可以御今，雖處於今，可以知古始，故不出戶闚牖而可知也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無在於一，而求之於眾也，道視之不可見，聽之不可聞，搏之不可得，如其知之，不須出戶，若其不知，出愈遠愈迷也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "得物之致，故雖不行而慮可知也。識物之宗，故雖不見，而是非之理可得而名也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 5,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "明物之性，因之而已。故雖不為而使之成矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
